The paper deals with joint source channel coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves coding techniques for transmitting data over a multiple access channel (MAC), which falls under the category of communication and networking (cs.MM). The use of concatenated coding schemes and outer codes suggests a focus on error correction and coding theory (cs.SI). The analysis of information theoretic performance involves the study of sufficient conditions, which is a common approach in network information theory (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with a specific example and proposes a new coding technique, which could be considered a contribution to computer science theory (cs.CC).
